headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 25 points, Kelly Oubre Jr. added 22 and the Charlotte Hornets held off a furious fourth-quarter rally by Bradley Beal and the Wizards to hand Washington its fifth loss in the last six games, 117-116 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Hornets hold on to beat Wizards 117-116

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 34 points, rookie A.J. Griffin tied a career high with 24 subbing for injured Trae Young and the short-handed Atlanta Hawks beat the Denver Nuggets 117-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 34 points, short-handed Hawks beat Nuggets

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 28 points, Tyler Herro had 26 and the Miami Heat completed a split of two games in Boston, beating the Celtics 120-116 on Friday night after Jaylen Brown <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo, Herro lead Heat over Celtics after Brown forces OT

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 27 points and the Brooklyn Nets built a huge lead before beating the Toronto Raptors 114-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets build huge lead, beat Raptors 114-105 for 4th straight

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 34 points and Evan Mobley had 19 points and 13 rebounds, lifting the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 107-96 victory over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis and LeBron James tore apart the NBA's top-rated defense and gave Los Angeles Lakers coach Darvin Ham a triumphant return to Milwaukee.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 44, LeBron passes Magic as Lakers beat Bucks

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 28 points and eight rebounds, Jaren Jackson Jr. added 22 points and four blocks — one in the closing minute — and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Philadelphia 76ers 117-109 on Friday night.

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 30 points and matched a career high with 15 rebounds, and the New Orleans Pelicans rolled to a 117-99 victory Friday night over the San Antonio Spurs, who were without coach Gregg Popovich.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson powers Pelicans past Popovich-less Spurs, 117-99

headlines.description: — Jalen Green sccored 30 points to jolt the Houston Rockets' offense and even managed to slow down the scorching Devin Booker — at least a little.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets rally from 16 down to beat Booker, Suns 122-121

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 24 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Utah Jazz to a 139-119 victory over the Indiana Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen, Kessler help Jazz overwhelm Pacers 139-119

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Draymond Green is healthy and back to his elite level of doing a bit of everything on both ends, even leading the offense with the second unit. He just missed his first triple-double of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poole scores 30 points with seven 3s off bench, Warriors win
